    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="522"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.34/4–2346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 26, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>223. Your 416 Apr 23.<note n="36" xml:id="d522fn36">Not printed, but see footnote
                        32, above.</note> Sale by Navy of heavier vessels to Chile must await
                    enabling legislation. It is hoped that such legislation may be submitted to
                    Congress in the near future. Pending passage of legislation impossible set any
                    date for sale or cost of vessels desired by Chile. Navy Dept advises cannot for
                    personnel and budgetary reasons hold open to Chile offer of small vessels
                    enumerated in <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 206, Apr. 12. Understand
                    Navy Dept has telegraphed Chief of US Mission in above sense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
